{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"523114c2-9926-480e-8e7e-319ef34483b1","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net test project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\nKeep your existing `xunit` 2.9.3 package as-is.\n\n**2. Enable MTP** in your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained apps):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --help\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` ≥ 1.0.0 is the MTP equivalent of `xunit.runner.visualstudio`.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n- If you use any VSTest-specific adapters/runsettings, you'll need to migrate those to MTP equivalents (e.g., `--report-trx` for TRX output).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1df449c9-da54-415f-8016-50a9ee1c10e8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":428},"id":"b761355a-f16a-462d-bd67-a45847b4ddc4","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:41:42.059Z","parentId":"172cf11e-2635-4b54-a928-2ae4eb0eabe2"}
